‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§Hello, I have some suggestions about traveling to China that I hope will be helpful to you.
If you like cities that blend modern and historical elements, please visit Xi'an and Beijing.
If you like food and culture, please go to: Chengdu, Chongqing, Guangzhou, Hangzhou, Nanjing
If you like modern cities, please go to: Shanghai, Shenzhen
If you like natural scenery, please go to: Huashan Mountain in Shaanxi Province (near Xi'an), Mount Huangshan Mountain in Anhui Province, Jiuzhaigou Valley Scenic and Historic Interest Area Valley in Sichuan Province, Yulong Snow Mountain in Lijiang, Yunnan Province, Zhangjiajie City, Hunan Province, Guilin, Guangxi Province

snippet.textDisplay: I would hope that most viewers are sophisticated enough to realize that central Shanghai is absolutely NOT the real China. Its like visiting Times Square or the strip in Vegas and saying that you are in the REAL US. Once you travel even 10km from the center of any Chinese city you will see a VASTLY different country. China is still a country where the vast majority of people are poor and living on less than $1000 per month. Hundreds of millions live on $100 per month or less. Disclosure: I am a European who has been living in China for the past 15 years. The number of tourists visiting China has declined by 97% compared to 2019 as a result of the pandemic and the myriad of anti spying national security laws. It may look safe at first glance but it an extremely tightly controlled police society. Don't be fooled!
